-- Navistar adopts tax asset protection plan 
-- By Mridhula Raghavan in Bangalore
-- Tue Jun 24, 2014 07:32AM EDT
-- None



June 24 (Reuters) - Truck and engine maker Navistar International Corp <NAV.N> said it would turn its existing poison pill takeover defense into a tax asset protection plan.

The tax asset protection plan is designed to discourage any person or group from acquiring more than 4.99 percent of stake, the company said on Tuesday. [ID:nPn551Qfm]  The existing poison pill exempted any person or group from owning more than 19.99 percent of the company's common stock.